    • Constructor Detail

      • TestRun

        public TestRun(java.lang.String id,
               java.lang.String creationDate,
               Outcome outcome,
               java.util.List<TestedClass> classList,
               int totalTests,
               int executedTests,
               int passedTests,
               int failedTests)
        throws TdaDataModelException
        Creates a new TestRun.
        Parameters:
        id - the TestRun's ID. Mustn't be null or empty.
        creationDate - the TestRun's creation date in the form "2016-09-21T13:37:43.7071946+02:00".
        outcome - the TestRun's outcome. Mustn't be null.
        classList - the TestRun's list of tested classes. Mustn't be null or empty.
        totalTests - the TestRun's number of total tests. Mustn't be below one.
        executedTests - the TestRun's number of executed tests. Mustn't be below zero.
        passedTests - the TestRun's number of passed tests. Mustn't be below zero.
        failedTests - the TestRun's number of failed tests. Mustn't be below zero.
        Throws:
        TdaDataModelException - if any of the arguments is not valid.
